Interface TreeDataStructure

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    TreeDataHandler

    public interface TreeDataStructure
    This interface is used to define the default behaviors that are required for a tree data structure to implement for use with this application.

      • addNode

        boolean addNode(Users parentNode,
                Users child)
        This method adds a new node into the tree, invokes the tree model's inserNodeInto internally to trigger the appropriate event for the JTree. Requires JTree to make new node visible.
        Parameters:
        parentNode - parent of the node that will be added
        child - the node that will be added to the tree model
        Returns:
        true if the node was added.
